/usr/include/c++/6.0.0/bits/basic_string.h: In function 'double std::__cxx11::stod(const string&, std::size_t*)': /usr/include/c++/6.0.0/bits/basic_string.h:5443:31: error: 'strtod_ASL' is not a member of 'std' { return __gnu_cxx::__stoa(&std::strtod, "stod", __str.c_str(), __idx); } ^~~
Looks like there is a #define strtod strtod_ASL somewhere which needs to go away or be renamed.

The problem was in the mp package, that had some 199x code and was incorrectly detecting the environment, and thinking it should provide a strtod function.
